Basic Git Notions
-Local Version Controls: saves file on one computer. 
-Centralized Version Control: saves changes to a shared server.
-Distributed Version Control:  dvc clients have complete backups of all the files on the personal computer. Changes are upload to a centralized server when every the connection is made. Each local has acess to the historic changes.  

Files States
-Git saves all these files as a comprressed directory which are modifiable in a workdir. One can notify that changes in the staging area chould be commited. 
Modified Files: recently changes.
Staged Files: marked to be saved.
Committed Files: have been saved.

Basic Flow:
$ brew update
$ brew doctor 
  -- check for possible problems that may occur
$ brew install git
$ echo 'export PATH="/usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:~/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bash_profile
   -- tell bash to look in the correct path for the homebrew managed version and restart terminal app
   
$ cd $HOME; vim .gitconfig
  -- create configuration file in home directory for variables.
$ git config --global user.name "John Doe"
$ git config --global user.email johndoe@example.com
$ git config --global core.editor vim
